This file tracks the status of releases in the 1.0.x line.

See "Stabilizing and maintaining releases" in trunk/HACKING for
details on how release lines and voting work, what kinds of bugs can
delay a release, etc.

Status of 1.0.9:
================

Candidate changes:

  * r11137
    Fix the verbose log code for revisions with no changed paths.
    Justification:
      Shallow silly bug.
    Votes:
      +1: bliss, lundblad

  * r11143,11145
    Fix broken RPM build caused by changes to book Makefile right before
    1.0.7 was released.
    Justification:
      Broken builds are bad.
    Votes:
      +1: david

  * r11211
    Fix performance regression for ls/RA->get_dir over ra_rav.
    Justification:
      Positively huge performance regression.
    Notes:
      To apply the patch:
      1. replace svn_repos__fs_revision_prop with svn_repos_fs_revision_prop
         and fix the indentation in subversion/mod_dav_svn/liveprops.c
      2. Run "svn merge -r11210:11211 http://svn.collab.net/repos/svn/trunk ."
      3. replace svn_repos_fs_revision_prop with svn_repos__fs_revision_prop
         and fix the indentation in subversion/mod_dav_svn/liveprops.c
    Votes:
      +1: bliss
